us aims, we will isolate anticipated CART-\nimmune/stromal cells PIC pairs from murine and patient blood and tissue\nsamples, focusing on B cells and immune-stromal cells, such as\nsynoviocytes in RA or epithelial glomerular cells in SLE, expressing\nBCMA^43,44^. In addition to PIC-seq, we will computationally model the\ninteractome of cells utilizing NicheNet, a bioinformatic framework\ncomprising a comprehensive database of ligand-receptor interactions and\ncorresponding changes in downstream targets, to investigate cellular\ninteractions^45^.", "chunk_index": 0, "element_type": null, "page_number": null}]
